  "decision_conditions": [
    "The proposed rear dormers, by reason of their siting in this open visually prominent position, cumulative size, scale, bulk and design would result in an incongruous, bulky, dominant and visually intrusive addition that would fail to harmonise with the architectural composition of the original dwelling, would be detrimental to the character, appearance and visual amenities of the street scene and the surrounding area. Therefore, the proposal would be contrary to Policy BE1 of the Hillingdon Local Plan: Part One - Strategic Policies (November 2012) and Policies DMHB 11, DMHB 12 and DMHD 1 of the Hillingdon Local Plan: Part Two - Development Management Policies (January 2020).",
    "The proposed rear dormers, by reasons of their siting, size, scale, design and proximity, would be detrimental to the amenities of the adjoining occupier at 2 Three Oaks Close by way of overlooking and loss of privacy. Therefore, the proposal would be contrary to Policies DMHB 11 and DMHD 1 of the Hillingdon Local Plan: Part Two - Development Management Policies (2020)."
